reason.tex:
%text The volume of the tank is 8 $m^3$. \[ \quad \therefore (2m)\times (x\cdot y) = 8 m^3 \implies xy = 4 m^2 \]
Moreover, we have to build \underline\text{one base} and \underline\text{four faces}. The tank is open from the top, remember?
The total cost of doing that will be % \begin{align} C = 70\cdot (xy) &+ \underbrace{2\cdot 45\cdot (2x) + 2\cdot 45\cdot 2y} _{\text{Two faces each with widths x and y}} \\ \text{But }x\cdot y &= 4 \\ \therefore C &= 280 + 180\cdot (x+y) \end{align}

\begin{align}
\frac{dC}{dx} = 180-\frac{720}{x^2} = 0&\implies x^2 = 4 \text{ or } x = 2\\
\text{Also }\frac{d^2 C}{dx^2} &\gt 0 \text{ for all }x \gt 0 
\end{align} 
%text

Hence, we will have \underline\text{minimum cost} 
when $x=2m$ and $y=\frac{4}{x} = 2m$. 

And the minimum cost will be 

%
\begin{align}
C &= 280 + 180\cdot (x+y) \\ 
&= 280 + 180\cdot (2+2) = ₹ 1000 
\end{align}
